@DOHgovph So, what if you are not experiencing those side effects after the vaccination? Would DOH please explain?

These are signs that your body is building up the immune response from the vaccine. These symptoms usually resolve in one to three days.

Know the answers to Frequently Asked Questions on how to manage common COVID-19 side effects.

- tenderness, pain, warmth, redness, itching or swelling on the arm where you got the injection  
- generally feeling of being unwell
- feeling tired (fatigue) 
- chills or feeling feverish
- headache
- joint pain or muscle ache https://t.co/GbrmgYDMu6
